What is Canvas?
Canvas is a widely used learning management system adopted by thousands of educational institutions worldwide. The platform allows students to complete lessons virtually, access course materials, and complete assignments at their own pace. While this provides flexibility to students, it also comes with its own set of challenges.

Canvas provides study materials through various formats including quizzes and assignments. The system tracks student progress and provides feedback through automated systems.

Challenges of Learning with Canvas
Despite its widespread adoption, students often face several challenges when using Canvas:

1. Time-Consuming Content: Many students find themselves spending excessive time on course materials that could be processed more efficiently.

2. Repetitive Assignments: The platform often requires students to complete similar assignments that don't necessarily enhance learning.

3. Limited Feedback: Automated systems may not provide the detailed feedback students need to improve their understanding.

4. Rigid Structure: The one-size-fits-all approach doesn't always accommodate different learning styles and paces.

